The food is good and deserves more than one star, but the wait staff is horrendous. I've been there several times and there is always an issue. Once, a waitress was chastising a cook for having not paid her back and yelling at him for always asking to borrow money. Lol. Another time a female server rolled her eyes and was visibly frustrated with an elderly couple sitting next to me. Another time we waited at the front for about 10 minutes only to finally be acknowledged and told that the tables were all sat and they were "too busy." No wait time was given and the best part was as we were waiting guests were also frustrated that they hadn't received their check. SO, there would have been a table if staff was present. The wait staff is always frustrated and rushing around. You should go for the possibility of entertaining drama, but be prepared to wait at the front desk for several minutes before anyone acknowledges your obvious presence. Then they will undoubtedly shrug you off to a table where you will probably do more waiting while simultaneously hearing complaining from both staff and guests. You might be lucky enough to observe some personal drama. If they do bring your food out it will be good. I've never been disappointed with the cooks. I'd give them 4 stars, but after all of the issues with the front staff a one star will suffice in place of visible hostility to the front staff.

This place has a real mom and pop feel to it. Cute and cozy. 16 tables inside and a few on the sidewalk. Very clean and bright. The staff is friendly and service is prompt.============================================================================= Hours as of this writing are 7:00AM to 2:30PM =============================================================================== Breakfast <$7.00 You can get 1 egg and toast for $2.00 or go with a Santa Fe omelet for $6.95 I had the biscuits and gravy (full portion) with 2 eggs on top and coffee. $8.68 after tax. ============================================================================= Lunch <$8.00. Small house salad is $2.25 and a grilled cheese is $3.50. If your exceptionally hungry, go for the Philly cheese steak sandwich for $7.50. ============================================================================= The menu has a wide selection and there are humorous titles throughout. . The proximity to the courthouse and litany of law offices nearby make this a good place to meet lawyers and maybe a judge or two. . In the early AM a small group of local business owners and folks who start earlier than most gather here and are quite entertaining to listen to. They have all the latest info about whats happening downtown. What court cases are hot and who has been busted for what
